      "body": "Stacked on https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/30597 and whats under it. See [this commit](https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/30610/commits/4a4600e8334aab58b20ff328abe697ad94a6e0fb).\r\n\r\nWith this change, the initial values for console patching settings are propagated from hook (which is the source of truth now, because of https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/30596). Instead of reading from `localStorage` the frontend is now requesting it from the hook. This happens when frontend is rendered (for browser extension it is the first time when user opens one of RDT's panels). Also, this is happening even if settings modal is not opened yet, so we have enough time to fetch this data without displaying loader or similar UI.\r\n\r\nThis 2-way pass `Frontend -> Backend -> Agent -> Hook -> Agent -> Backend -> Frontend` takes ~40ms for browser extension.",
